Definition: [Ἀσύγκριτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g4793}}; incomparable; Asyncritus, a Christian
[ἄστρον] neuter from {{g792}}; properly, a constellation; put for a single star (natural or artificial)
[ἀστεῖος] from ἄστυ (a city); urbane, i.e. (by implication) handsome
[ἀστατέω] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2476}}; to be non-stationary, i.e. (figuratively) homeless
[ἀστήρικτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g4741}}; unfixed, i.e. (figuratively) vacillating
[ἀστήρ] probably from the base of {{g4766}}; a star (as strown over the sky), literally or figuratively
[ἀστοχέω] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and στοίχος (an aim); to miss the mark, i.e. (figuratively) deviate from truth
[ἄστοργος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of στέργω (to cherish affectionately); hard-hearted towards kindred
[ἀστράπτω] probably from  {{g792}}; to flash as lightning
[ἀστραπή] from {{g797}}; lightning; by analogy, glare
[Ἀριστόβουλος] from the same as {{g712}} and {{g1012}}; best counselling; Aristoboulus, a Christian
[ἀριστερός] apparently a comparative of the same as {{g712}}; the left hand (as second-best)
[ἀρκετός] from {{g714}}; satisfactory
[ἄριστον] apparently neuter of a superlative from the same as {{g730}}; the best meal (or breakfast; perhaps from ἦρι ("early")), i.e. luncheon
[ἄρκτος] probably from {{g714}}; a bear (as obstructing by ferocity)
[ἀρκέω] apparently a primary verb (but probably akin to {{g142}} through the idea of raising a barrier); properly, to ward off, i.e. (by implication) to avail (figuratively, be satisfactory)
[Ἀρμαγεδδών] of Hebrew origin ({{h2022}} and {{h4023}}); Armageddon (or Har-Meggiddon), a symbolic name
[ἅρμα] probably from {{g142}} (perhaps with {{g1}} (as a particle of union) prefixed); a chariot (as raised or fitted together (compare {{g719}}))
[ἁρμός] from the same as {{g716}}; an articulation (of the body)
[ἁρμόζω] from {{g719}}; to joint, i.e. (figuratively) to woo (reflexively, to betroth)
[ἀσύμφωνος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g4859}}; inharmonious (figuratively)
[ἀσεβέω] from {{g765}}; to be (by implied act) impious or wicked
[ἀσεβής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g4576}}; irreverent, i.e. (by extension) impious or wicked
[ἀσέλγεια] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed σελγής (of uncertain derivation, but apparently meaning continent); licentiousness (sometimes including other vices)
[ἄσημος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{g4591}}; unmarked, i.e. (figuratively) ignoble
[Ἀσά] of Hebrew origin ({{h609}}); Asa, an Israelite
[ἀσάλευτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g4531}}; unshaken, i.e. (by implication) immovable (figuratively)
[ἄσβεστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g4570}}; not extinguished, i.e. (by implication) perpetual
[ἀσέβεια] from {{g765}}; impiety, i.e. (by implication) wickedness
[Ἀσήρ] of Hebrew origin ({{h836}}); Aser (i.e. Asher), an Israelite tribe
[ἀσθένεια] from {{g772}}; feebleness (of mind or body); by implication, malady; morally, frailty
[ἄσιτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g4621}}; without (taking) food
[ἀσιτία] from {{g777}}; fasting (the state)
[Ἀσιάρχης] from {{g773}} and {{g746}}; an Asiarch or president of the public festivities in a city of Asia Minor
[Ἀσιανός] from {{g773}}; an Asian (i.e. Asiatic) or an inhabitant of Asia
[Ἀσία] of uncertain derivation; Asia, i.e. Asia Minor, or (usually) only its western shore
[ἀσθενής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{g4599}}; strengthless (in various applications, literal, figurative and moral)
[ἀσθένημα] from {{g770}}; a scruple of conscience
[ἀσθενέω] from {{g772}}; to be feeble (in any sense)
[ἀσκός] from the same as {{g778}}; a leathern (or skin) bag used as a bottle
[ἀσκέω] probably from the same as {{g4632}}; to elaborate, i.e. (figuratively) train (by implication, strive)
[Ἀρφαξάδ] of Hebrew origin ({{h775}}); Arphaxad, a post-diluvian patriarch
[ἀρχάγγελος] from {{g757}} and {{g32}}; a chief angel
[ἄρτος] from {{g142}}; bread (as raised) or a loaf
[ἀρτύω] from a presumed derivative of {{g142}}; to prepare, i.e. spice (with stimulating condiments)
[ἀρχή] from {{g756}}; (properly abstract) a commencement, or (concretely) chief (in various applications of order, time, place, or rank)
[ἀρχηγός] from {{g746}} and {{g71}}; a chief leader
[ἀρχαῖος] from {{g746}}; original or primeval
[Ἀρχέλαος] from {{g757}} and {{g2994}}; people-ruling; Archelaus, a Jewish king
[ἀρχιερατικός] from {{g746}} and a derivative of {{g2413}}; high-priestly
[ἀρχιερεύς] from {{g746}} and {{g2409}}; the high-priest (literally, of the Jews, typically, Christ); by extension a chief priest
[ἄρωμα] from {{g142}} (in the sense of sending off scent); an aromatic
[ἄρχων] present participle of {{g757}}; a first (in rank or power)
[ἀρχιτρίκλινος] from {{g746}} and a compound of {{g5140}} and {{g2827}} (a dinner-bed, because composed of three couches); director of the entertainment
[ἀρχιτελώνης] from {{g746}} and {{g5057}}; a principle tax-gatherer
[ἄρχω] a primary verb; to be first (in political rank or power)
[ἄρχομαι] middle voice of {{g757}} (through the implication, of precedence); to commence (in order of time)
[Ἄρχιππος] from {{g746}} and {{g2462}}; horse-ruler; Archippus, a Christian
[ἀρχιποίμην] from {{g746}} and {{g4166}}; a head shepherd
[ἀρχιτέκτων] from {{g746}} and {{g5045}}; a chief constructor, i.e. "architect"
[ἀρχισυνάγωγος] from {{g746}} and {{g4864}}; director of the synagogue services
[ἀῤῥαβών] of Hebrew origin ({{h6162}}); a pledge, i.e. part of the purchase-money or property given in advance as security for the rest
[ἄῤῥαφος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of the same as {{g4476}}; unsewed, i.e. of a single piece
[ἀρνέομαι] perhaps from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the middle voice of {{g4483}}; to contradict, i.e. disavow, reject, abnegate
[ἀρνίον] diminutive from {{g704}}; a lambkin
[ἀροτριόω] from {{g723}}; to plow
[ἄροτρον] from ἀρόω (to till); a plow
[ἁρπαγή] from {{g726}}; pillage (properly abstract)
[ἁρπαγμός] from {{g726}}; plunder (properly concrete)
[ἁρπάζω] from a derivative of {{g138}}; to seize (in various applications)
[ἅρπαξ] from {{g726}}; rapacious
[ἄρτιος] from {{g737}}; fresh, i.e. (by implication) complete
[ἀρτιγέννητος] from {{g737}} and {{g1084}}; just born, i.e. (figuratively) a young convert
[ἀρσενοκοίτης] from {{g730}} and {{g2845}}; a sodomite
[ἄῤῥωστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g4517}}; infirm
[ἄῤῥητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the same as {{g4490}}; unsaid, i.e. (by implication) inexpressible
[ἄῤῥην]   or ἄρσηνprobably from {{g142}}; male (as stronger for lifting)
[ἄρτι] adverb from a derivative of {{g142}} (compare {{g740}}) through the idea of suspension; just now

[ἀρτέμων] from a derivative of {{g737}}; properly, something ready (or else more remotely from {{g142}} (compare {{g740}}); something hung up), i.e. (specially) the topsail (rather foresail or jib) of a vessel
[Ἄρτεμις] probably from the same as {{g736}}; prompt; Artemis, the name of a Grecian goddess borrowed by the Asiatics for one of their deities
[Ἀρτεμάς] contracted from a compound of {{g735}} and {{g1435}}; gift of Artemis; Artemas (or Artemidorus), a Christian
[ἆσσον] neuter comparative of the base of {{g1451}}; more nearly, i.e. very near
[Ἄσσος] probably of foreign origin; Assus, a city of Asia MInor
[ἄσπονδος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g4689}}; literally, without libation (which usually accompanied a treaty), i.e. (by implication) truceless
[ἀσσάριον] of Latin origin; an assarius or as, a Roman coin
[ἄσπιλος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g4695}}; unblemished (physically or morally)
[ἀσπίς] of uncertain derivation; a buckler (or round shield); used of a serpent (as coiling itself), probably the "asp"
[ἀσπάζομαι] from {{g1}} (as a particle of union) and a presumed form of {{g4685}}; to enfold in the arms, i.e. (by implication) to salute, (figuratively) to welcome
[ἀσπασμός] from {{g782}}; a greeting (in person or by letter)
[ἀσμένως] adverb from a derivative of the base of {{g2237}}; with pleasure
[ἄσοφος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g4680}}; unwise
[ἀριθμός] from {{g142}}; a number (as reckoned up)
[Ἀριμαθαία] of Hebrew origin ({{h7414}}); Arimathæa (or Ramah), a place in Palestine
[ἀρήν] perhaps the same as {{g730}}; a lamb (as a male)
[ἀριθμέω] from {{g706}}; to enumerate or count
[Ἀρέτας] of foreign origin; Aretas, an Arabian
[ἀρέτη] from the same as {{g730}}; properly, manliness (valor), i.e. excellence (intrinsic or attributed)
[ἀρεστός] from {{g700}}; agreeable; by implication, fit
[Ἀρίσταρχος] from the same as {{g712}} and {{g757}}; best ruling; Aristarchus, a Macedonian
[ἀριστάω] from {{g712}}; to take the principle meal
